    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nN/A\n\n### Feature description\n\nThis is something between (regression) bug or feature request. \r\n\r\n## python remote plugins\r\n\r\nWhen remote (python) plugin throws an error or exception *during an execution of pynvim(neovim) API*, there is no much debugging information available.\r\n\r\nFor example,\r\n\r\n```\r\npython3-rplugin-host: Async request caused an error:\r\nInvalid buffer id: 421\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n```\r\n\r\nwithout information about (i) such a neovim API (e.g., `vim.async_call`) is called by which remote plugin, nor (ii) stacktrace of the plugin.\r\n\r\nNote that when a python exception is raised (from the python remote plugin), it correctly prints the stack trace:\r\n```\r\nerror caught in async handler '.../vim/plugged/some-plugin/rplugin/python3/some_module:function:SomeCommand [args]'\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  ...\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Lua plugins\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to a lua plugin, sometimes the whole stacktrace are printed in a single line:\r\n\r\nFor example (this bug is not specific to fidget.nvim; it's just one example),\r\n\r\n```\r\nError detected while processing function clever_f#find_with[44]..<SNR>175_getchar:                                                                     \r\nline    2:\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /Users/wookayin/.vim/plugged/fidget.nvim/lua/fidget.lua:190: E523: Not allowed here^@stack traceback:^@^I[C]: in func\r\ntion 'nvim_open_win'^@^I/Users/wookayin/.vim/plugged/fidget.nvim/lua/fidget.lua:190: in function 'show'^@^I/Users/wookayin/.vim/plugged/fidget.nvim/lua/fidget.l\r\nua:55: in function </Users/wookayin/.vim/plugged/fidget.nvim/lua/fidget.lua:51>\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhere the stacktrace message is printed without actual carriage return but a literal character `^@^I`. I remember this was not the case at some earlier neovim versions (like v0.5), but since some point neovim started to print the stacktrace in a difficult-to-read format.",
