            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "An example with\n```\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev                                                                                    \nBuild type: Debug                                                                                   \nLuaJIT 2.1.1727870382                                                                               \n```\nSource the following and hit any key\n```\nlocal function F2()\n    error(\"in F2()\")\nend\nlocal function F1()\n    F2()\nend\nlocal function handler()\n    F1()\nend\nvim.on_key(handler)\n```\noutput for `stack traceback` has no stack for the callback.\n```\nError executing  vim.on_key Lua callback: vim/_editor.lua:0: Error executing 'on_key' with ns_ids '14'\n    Messages: [string \":source (no file)\"]:2: in F2()\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'error'\n        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n-----\n@zeertzjq @justinmk This is labeled `enhancement`. Isn't not getting a stack trace a bug?",
